      {
        "annotationType": "ANNOTATION",
        "comment": {
          "commentType": "CATALYTIC ACTIVITY",
          "reaction": {
            "name": "ATP + [prokaryotic ubiquitin-like protein]-L-glutamate + [protein]-L-lysine = ADP + phosphate + N(6)-([prokaryotic ubiquitin-like protein]-gamma-L-glutamyl)-[protein]-L-lysine.",
            "reactionCrossReferences": [],
            "ecNumber": "6.3.1.19"
          }
        }
      },
      {
        "annotationType": "ANNOTATION",
        "comment": {
          "commentType": "MISCELLANEOUS",
          "texts": [
            {
              "value": "The reaction mechanism probably proceeds via the activation of Pup by phosphorylation of its C-terminal glutamate, which is then subject to nucleophilic attack by the substrate lysine, resulting in an isopeptide bond and the release of phosphate as a good leaving group"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "annotationType": "ANNOTATION",
        "comment": {
          "commentType": "FUNCTION",
          "texts": [
            {
              "value": "Catalyzes the covalent attachment of the prokaryotic ubiquitin-like protein modifier Pup to the proteasomal substrate proteins, thereby targeting them for proteasomal degradation. This tagging system is termed pupylation. The ligation reaction involves the side-chain carboxylate of the C-terminal glutamate of Pup and the side-chain amino group of a substrate lysine"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "annotationType": "ANNOTATION",
        "comment": {
          "commentType": "PATHWAY",
          "texts": [
            {
              "value": "Protein degradation; proteasomal Pup-dependent pathway"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "annotationType": "ANNOTATION",
        "comment": {
          "commentType": "PATHWAY",
          "texts": [
            {
              "value": "Protein modification; protein pupylation"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "annotationType": "ANNOTATION",
        "comment": {
          "commentType": "SIMILARITY",
          "texts": [
            {
              "value": "Belongs to the Pup ligase/Pup deamidase family. Pup-conjugating enzyme subfamily"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
